<%=EndAppModParaFont%>



<%=AppModParaFont%>
&#149;	Concentrate on earning the High S leader's trust.<br>
&#149;	Focus more on providing facts, details, and substance than you usually do.<br>
&#149;	Express sincere appreciation for your leader's efforts and contributions.<br>
&#149;	Be less impulsive and more deliberate than you usually are.<br>
&#149;	Tone down your natural exuberance.<br>
&#149;	Don't push too aggressively or demand what you want.<br>
&#149;	Don't move too fast. Give plenty of warning about needed changes.<br>
&#149;	Ask "how" questions, elicit feedback, and listen attentively.<br>
